+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UeY7JPPwkjmUET4Rx8Hto8","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the complete codebase analysis.\n\n---\n\n## Complete Codebase Report\n\n### Project Overview\n\nThis is a **Notes API** built with **Express + SQLite** (via `better-sqlite3`). It is an ES module TypeScript project that currently has CRUD endpoints for notes. The task (per `TASK.md`) is to **add full-text search using SQLite FTS5**.\n\n---\n\n### File Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n  package.json\n  tsconfig.json\n  vitest.config.ts\n  .eslintrc.cjs\n  .gitignore\n  TASK.md\n  src/\n    db.ts\n    models.ts\n    routes.ts\n    errors.ts\n    server.ts\n    seed.ts\n  tests/\n    notes.test.ts\n    search.test.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n### 1. `/workspace/src/db.ts` -- Database Setup\n\n- **`createDatabase(path?)`**: Creates a `better-sqlite3` database (in-memory if no path provided). Sets `journal_mode = WAL` and `foreign_keys = ON`. Creates the `notes` table:\n  ```sql\n  CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS notes (\n    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n    title TEXT NOT NULL,\n    body TEXT NOT NULL,\n    tags TEXT DEFAULT '[]',\n    created_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n    updated_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n  )\n  ```\n- **`seedDatabase(db)`**: Inserts seed notes (via `getSeedNotes()`) using a transaction.\n- **`getSeedNotes()`**: Returns an array of **50 sample notes** covering topics like programming (TypeScript, Python, Rust, React, Docker, Kubernetes, etc.), cooking, travel, science, music, health, photography, and more. Each note has `title`, `body`, and `tags` (JSON-stringified array).\n\n**Key observation**: There is **no FTS5 virtual table** created yet. This needs to be added.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `/workspace/src/models.ts` -- TypeScript Interfaces\n\n```typescript\ninterface Note {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags: string;        // JSON array stored as string\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\ninterface NoteInput {\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n}\n\ninterface SearchResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  snippet: string;     // with <mark> highlighting\n  rank: number;\n}\n\ninterface SuggestResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n}\n```\n\n`SearchResult` and `SuggestResult` are already defined but not yet used anywhere.\n\n---\n\n### 3. `/workspace/src/routes.ts` -- Existing Routes\n\nFive CRUD endpoints, all using Express `Router`:\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| `GET` | `/notes` | List all notes (optional `?tag=X` filter via `json_each`) |\n| `GET` | `/notes/:id` | Get single note by ID (404 if not found) |\n| `POST` | `/notes` | Create note (validates title and body required; 400 on missing) |\n| `PUT` | `/notes/:id` | Update note (partial update; 404 if not found) |\n| `DELETE` | `/notes/:id` | Delete note (204 on success; 404 if not found) |\n\n**Key observation**: There are **no search or suggest routes** yet. Two new routes need to be added:\n- `GET /notes/search?q=<query>`\n- `GET /notes/search/suggest?q=<prefix>`\n\n**Important routing note**: The search routes (`/notes/search` and `/notes/search/suggest`) must be registered **before** `/notes/:id`, otherwise Express will interpret `\"search\"` as an `:id` parameter.\n\n---\n\n### 4. `/workspace/src/errors.ts` -- Error Handling\n\nTwo custom error classes:\n- **`NotFoundError`** (status 404)\n- **`ValidationError`** (status 400)\n\n**`errorHandler`** middleware: Catches errors passed via `next(err)`, returns appropriate JSON responses. Unknown errors get a 500.\n\n---\n\n### 5. `/workspace/src/server.ts` -- Server Setup\n\n- **`createApp(dbPath?)`**: Creates database, Express app, registers JSON middleware, routes, and error handler. Returns `{ app, db }`.\n- **`createSeededApp(dbPath?)`**: Calls `createApp` then seeds the database. Returns `{ app, db }`.\n- Auto-starts on port 3000 (or `PORT` env) if run directly.\n\n**`App` interface**: `{ app: express.Express; db: Database.Database }`\n\n---\n\n### 6. `/workspace/src/seed.ts` -- Seed Script\n\nStandalone script that creates a database file (default `notes.db`), seeds it, prints count, and closes. Run via `npm run seed` (which executes `tsx src/seed.ts`).\n\n---\n\n### 7. `/workspace/tests/notes.test.ts` -- 15 Existing CRUD Tests\n\nUses `vitest` + `supertest`. Creates an in-memory app (via `createApp()`) for each test. Tests cover:\n\n1. `GET /notes` returns all notes\n2. `GET /notes/:id` returns specific note\n3. `GET /notes/:id` returns 404 for non-existent\n4. `POST /notes` creates note with title and body\n5. `POST /notes` creates note with tags\n6. `POST /notes` returns 400 without title\n7. `POST /notes` returns 400 without body\n8. `PUT /notes/:id` updates note\n9. `PUT /notes/:id` returns 404 for non-existent\n10. `DELETE /notes/:id` removes note\n11. `DELETE /notes/:id` returns 404 for non-existent\n12. `GET /notes?tag=X` filters by tag\n13. Notes have `created_at` timestamp\n14. Notes have `updated_at` timestamp\n15. PUT updates `updated_at` timestamp\n\n---\n\n### 8. `/workspace/tests/search.test.ts` -- 20 Search Tests (Currently Failing)\n\nUses `createSeededApp()` (the seeded version with ~50 notes). Tests cover:\n\n1. `GET /notes/search?q=keyword` returns matching notes\n2. Results have `snippet` field\n3. Snippets contain `<mark>` tags around matched terms\n4. Results are ranked by relevance (rank values in ascending order)\n5. Exact phrase matching with quoted phrases (`\"chocolate chip\"`)\n6. Search returns `id`, `title`, `snippet`, `rank` fields with correct types\n7. Non-existent term returns empty array\n8. Missing `q` parameter returns 400\n9. Empty `q` parameter returns 400\n10. Pagination: `page=1` returns first 20 results, response includes `page` and `perPage`\n11. Pagination: `page=2` returns next results\n12. Pagination response includes `total` count\n13. `GET /notes/search/suggest?q=prefix` returns up to 5 titles\n14. Suggest results match prefix in title\n15. `GET /notes/search/suggest?q=` returns 400\n16. FTS syncs on create -- new note appears in search\n17. FTS syncs on update -- updated content appears, old content disappears\n18. FTS syncs on delete -- deleted note disappears from search\n19. Special characters in query don't crash\n20. Search response time under 100ms\n\n---\n\n### 9. `/workspace/package.json` -- Dependencies & Scripts\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `better-sqlite3` ^11.0.0 -- SQLite binding\n- `express` ^4.21.0 -- HTTP framework\n\n**Dev Dependencies:**\n- `typescript` ^5.4.0\n- `vitest` ^2.0.0 -- Test runner\n- `eslint` ^8.56.0 + `@typescript-eslint` plugins\n- `@types/better-sqlite3`, `@types/express`, `@types/supertest`\n- `supertest` ^7.0.0 -- HTTP testing\n- `tsx` ^4.0.0 -- TypeScript execution\n\n**Scripts:**\n- `build`: `tsc`\n- `lint`: `eslint src/ tests/`\n- `test`: `vitest run`\n- `seed`: `tsx src/seed.ts`\n\n**Module type:** `\"type\": \"module\"` (ES modules)\n\n---\n\n### 10. Configuration Files\n\n**`/workspace/tsconfig.json`**: Targets ES2022, Node16 module resolution, strict mode, outputs to `./dist`.\n\n**`/workspace/vitest.config.ts`**: Globals enabled, 10-second test timeout.\n\n**`/workspace/.eslintrc.cjs`**: Uses `@typescript-eslint` parser and recommended rules. Allows unused args prefixed with `_`.\n\n**`/workspace/.gitignore`**: Ignores `node_modules/`, `dist/`, and `*.db`.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of What Needs to Be Implemented\n\nBased on `TASK.md` and the test expectations in `tests/search.test.ts`:\n\n1. **Create an FTS5 virtual table** in `src/db.ts` to index `title` and `body` columns of notes.\n\n2. **Populate the FTS5 table** when seeding (and keep it synced with the main `notes` table).\n\n3. **Add FTS sync logic** so that when notes are created, updated, or deleted via the CRUD routes, the FTS index stays in sync. This can be done via SQLite triggers or manual sync in the route handlers.\n\n4. **Add `GET /notes/search?q=<query>` route** in `src/routes.ts`:\n   - Query the FTS5 table using `MATCH`\n   - Return `{ results: SearchResult[], total, page, perPage }`\n   - Use `snippet()` FTS5 function with `<mark>` tags\n   - Use `rank` (BM25) for ordering\n   - Support pagination (20 per page, `?page=N`)\n   - Return 400 if `q` is missing or empty\n   - Handle special characters gracefully\n\n5. **Add `GET /notes/search/suggest?q=<prefix>` route**:\n   - Return up to 5 matching titles (prefix search using FTS5 prefix queries)\n   - Return `{ results: SuggestResult[] }`\n   - Return 400 if `q` is missing or empty\n\n6. **Ensure the search routes are registered before `/notes/:id`** to avoid route conflicts.\n\n7. **All 35 tests** (15 CRUD + 20 search) must pass."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a7ce682 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 32902\ntool_uses: 15\nduration_ms: 61371</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8fde5474-3571-4a5d-8033-44cfca3c9e62","uuid":"3e462d4b-650b-497c-a56f-d8a4ded6d358","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the full codebase structure. Read all source files in src/ and test files in tests/. I need to understand:\n1. The database setup in src/db.ts\n2. The models in src/models.ts\n3. The existing routes in src/routes.ts\n4. The error handling in src/errors.ts\n5. The server setup in src/server.ts\n6. The seed script in src/seed.ts\n7. The existing tests in tests/notes.test.ts\n8. The search tests in tests/search.test.ts\n9. The package.json for dependencies and scripts\n\nRead ALL these files completely and report their full contents.","agentId":"a7ce682","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the complete codebase analysis.\n\n---\n\n## Complete Codebase Report\n\n### Project Overview\n\nThis is a **Notes API** built with **Express + SQLite** (via `better-sqlite3`). It is an ES module TypeScript project that currently has CRUD endp